{"title_page": "Buaran railway station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n| name= Buaran Station\n| native_name= <small>Stasiun Baruan</small>\n| image=\n| image_size= \n| image_caption= \n| address= Jalan I Gusti Ngurah Rai, Penggilingan, [[Cakung]], [[East Jakarta]] 13940\n| country= [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates= {{coord|-6.215583|106.923215|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation= +11 m\n| line=\n| other=\n| platform=\n| tracks=\n| parking=\n| bicycle=\n| baggage_check=\n| passengers=\n| pass_year=\n| pass_percent=\n| pass_system=\n| opened=\n| rebuilt=\n| ADA=\n| code= BUA\n| owned=[[PT Kereta Api Indonesia]]\n| zone=\n| services={{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bekasi-Jakarta Kota|previous=Klender Baru|next=Klender}}\n| map_type=\n| mpassengers=\n}}\n\n'''Buaran station''' is a commuter rail station that is part of the [[KAI Commuter Jabodetabek]] system, and is located in Jl. I Gusti Ngurah Rai, Penggillingan, Cakung, East Jakarta, and is part of the rail system's \"Zone 1\". The elevation of this station is +11 m.\n\n==Trains and services==\nThe lines below are the lines that stop and serve in the Buaran station.\n*[[KAI Commuter Jabodetabek|Blue Line]]: to [[Jakarta Kota railway station|Jakarta Kota]] and [[Bekasi railway station|Bekasi]]\n\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|Jakarta}}\n[[Category:East Jakarta]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Jakarta]]\n\n\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name= Buaran Station\n| native_name= <small>Stasiun Baruan</small>\n| image=\n| image_size= \n| image_caption= \n| address= Jalan I Gusti Ngurah Rai, Penggilingan, [[Cakung]], [[East Jakarta]] 13940\n| country= [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates= {{coord|-6.215583|106.923215|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation= +11 m\n| line=\n| other=\n| platform=\n| tracks=\n| parking=\n| bicycle=\n| baggage_check=\n| passengers=\n| pass_year=\n| pass_percent=\n| pass_system=\n| opened=\n| rebuilt=\n| ADA=\n| code= BUA\n| owned=[[PT Kereta Api Indonesia]]\n| zone=\n| services={{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Bekasi-Jakarta Kota|previous=Klender Baru|next=Klender}}\n| map_type=\n| mpassengers=\n}}\n\n'''Buaran station''' is a commuter rail station that is part of the [[KAI Commuter Jabodetabek]] system, and is located in Jl. I Gusti Ngurah Rai, Penggillingan, Cakung, East Jakarta, and is part of the rail system's \"Zone 1\". The elevation of this station is +11 m.\n\n==Trains and services==\nThe lines below are the lines that stop and serve in the Buaran station.\n*[[KAI Commuter Jabodetabek|Blue Line]]: to [[Jakarta Kota railway station|Jakarta Kota]] and [[Bekasi railway station|Bekasi]]\n\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|Jakarta}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Jakarta]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:East JakartausingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buaran_railway_station"}
{"title_page": "Atofio Hrysafi", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Atofio Hrysafi<br>\u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9\n| type         = [[Album]]\n| artist       = [[Katy Garbi]]\n| cover        = ATOFIOXRUSAFI.jpg\n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = December 20, 1994\n| recorded     = City studio<br>Sierra studio\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop (music)|Pop]], [[La\u00efka|Modern Laika]], [[Dance music|Dance]]\n| length       = 36:39\n| language     = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music Greece]]<br>[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| producer     = Giannis Doulamis\n| prev_title   = [[Os Ton Paradeiso]]\n| prev_year    = 1993\n| next_title   = [[Arhizo Polemo]]\n| next_year    = 1996\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Atofio Hrysafi\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Ksypoliti Horevo]]\n | single1date = 1994\n | single2     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Atofio Hrysafi]]\n | single2date = 1994\n | single3     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Mi Me Sygkrineis]]\n | single3date = 1995\n | single4     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Kolasi]]\n | single4date = 1995\n | single5     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]]]\n | single5date = 1995\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' (''trans.'' \u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9; Pure Gold) is an album by popular [[Greece|Greek]] artist [[Katy Garbi]].\n\nIt was released on December 20, 1994 by [[Sony Music|Sony Music Greece]] and was certified 2x Platinum, selling over 120,000 units worldwide.<ref name=\"10+1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.getgreekmusic.gr/diskoi-garbi-afieroma/|title=el:10+1 \u03b1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c0\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9 \u03b4\u03af\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae!|date=2015-04-10|publisher=GetGreekMusic|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-02-12}}</ref> The album contains ten songs, five of which were composed by [[Kostas Tournas]] and five of which were composed by [[Phoebus (songwriter)|Phoebus]].<ref name=\"10+1tralala\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tralala.gr/viografia-keti-garmpi/|title=el:\u0392\u03b9\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1 {{!}} \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae|date=2018-06-08|publisher=Tralala Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-08}}</ref>\n\n== Track List ==\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed = \n| headline = \n| title1 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Ksypoliti Horevo]]\n| note1 = \u039e\u03c5\u03c0\u03cc\u03bb\u03c5\u03c4\u03b7 \u03a7\u03bf\u03c1\u03b5\u03cd\u03c9; I Dance Barefoot\n| lyrics1 = [[Kostas Tournas]]\n| music1 = Kostas Tournas\n| length1 = 4:13\n| title2 = I Agapas I Fevgeis\n| note2 = \u0389 \u0391\u03b3\u03b1\u03c0\u03ac\u03c2 \u0389 \u03a6\u03b5\u03cd\u03b3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2; To Love Or To Leave\n| lyrics2 = Kostas Tournas\n| music2 = Kostas Tournas\n| length2 = 3:11\n| title3 = Oti Oneirevomaste Ginetai\n| note3 = \u038c\u03c4\u03b9 \u039f\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5 \u0393\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9; Whatever Our Dreams Become\n| lyrics3 = Kostas Tournas\n| music3 = Kostas Tournas\n| length3 = 3:11\n| title4 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Mi Me Sygkrineis]]\n| note4 = \u039c\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5 \u03a3\u03c5\u03b3\u03ba\u03c1\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2; Don't Compare Me\n| lyrics4 = Kostas Tournas\n| music4 = Kostas Tournas\n| length4 = 4:03\n| title5 = Otan Se Ksehaso\n| note5 = \u038c\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd \u03a3\u03b5 \u039e\u03b5\u03c7\u03ac\u03c3\u03c9; When I Forget You\n| lyrics5 = Kostas Tournas\n| music5 = Kostas Tournas\n| length5 = 3:42\n| title6 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]]]\n| note6 = \u03a3\u03b5 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1 [\u03a0\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a0\u03b5\u03c2]; In Siege [Say It, Say It]\n| lyrics6 = [[Phoebus]]\n| music6 = Phoebus\n| length6 = 3:32\n| title7 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Kolasi]]\n| note7 = \u039a\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7; Hell\n| lyrics7 = Phoebus\n| music7 = Phoebus\n| length7 = 3:29\n| title8 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Atofio Hrysafi]]\n| note8 = \u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9; Pure Gold\n| lyrics8 = Phoebus\n| music8 = Phoebus\n| length8 = 3:25\n| title9 = O Ilios Pou Egine Vrohi\n| note9 = \u039f \u0389\u03bb\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 \u03a0\u03bf\u03c5 \u0388\u03b3\u03b9\u03bd\u03b5 \u0392\u03c1\u03bf\u03c7\u03ae; The Sun That Became Rain\n| lyrics9 = Phoebus\n| music9 = Phoebus\n| length9 = 3:47\n| title10 = Moiazo\n| note10 = \u039c\u03bf\u03b9\u03ac\u03b6\u03c9; I Resemble\n| lyrics10 = Phoebus\n| music10 = Phoebus\n| length10 = 4:06\n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Singles and Music Videos ==\nThe following singles were officially released to radio stations and made into music videos.\n\n#\"Ksypoliti Horevo\" <small>(I Dance Barefoot)</small>\n#\"Atofio Hrysafi\" <small>(Pure Gold)</small>\n#\"Mi Me Sygkrineis\" <small>(Don't Compare Me)</small>\n#\"Kolasi\" <small>(Hell)</small>\n#\"Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]\" <small>(In Siege [Say It, Say It])</small>\n\n== Credits and Personnel ==\n'''Personnel'''\n\n*<small>Arranged By:</small> Charis Andreadis <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</small>\n*<small>Backing Vocals:</small> Charis Chalkitis <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Nikos Logothetis <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Sofia Noiti <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Poimis Petrou <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Sandy Politi <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Dimitris Tsopanellis <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Martha Zioga <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5)</small>\n*<small>Baglama:</small> Giannis Mpithikotsis <small>(tracks: 9)</small>\n*<small>Bass:</small> Giotis Kiourtsoglou <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 4)</small>\n*<small>Bouzouki:</small> Giannis Mpithikotsis <small>(tracks: 9),</small> Thodoris Pasiaras <small>(tracks: 1, 4)</small>\n*<small>C\u00fcmb\u00fc\u015f:</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 10)</small>\n*<small>Guitars:</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1),</small> Akis Tourkogiorgis <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 4)</small>\n*<small>Keyboards, Programmed By:</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5),</small> Orestis Plakidis <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10)</small>\n*<small>Percussion:</small> Giorgos Notaras <small>(tracks: 1),</small> Giorgos Roilos <small>(tracks: 7, 8)</small>\n*<small>Saxophone:</small> Silvios Siros <small>(tracks: 5)</small>\n*<small>Second Vocal:</small> [[Katy Garbi]] <small>(tracks: 1, 4),</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 7, 9)</small>\n\n\n'''Production'''\n\n*<small>Artwork:</small> Giannis Doxas\n*<small>Executive Producer:</small> Giannis Doulamis\n*<small>Hair Styling:</small> Giannis Michailidis\n*<small>Make Up:</small> Achilleas Charitos\n*<small>Mastering:</small> Giannis Ioannidis [D.P.H.]\n*<small>Photographer:</small> Ntinos Diamantopoulos\n*<small>Recorded By, Mixed By:</small> Dimitris Malegkas [City studio] <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5),</small> Panagiotis Petronikolos [Sierra studio] <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Giannis Tountas [City studio] <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</small>\n\n== Accolades ==\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' was awarded \"Album of the Year\" at the [[Pop Corn Music Awards of 1995]].<ref name=\"GarbiMikrofono\">{{cite web|url=https://mikrofwno.gr/2019/06/kaiti-garmpi-i-foni-tis-kardias-mas/|title=el:\u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae: \u0397 \u03c6\u03c9\u03bd\u03ae \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b9\u03ac\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2|date=2019-06-01|publisher=Mikrofono Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-08}}</ref> Another award was received for \"Best Folk Dance Track\" (Ksypoliti Horevo) the same year.\n\n==Certifications==\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' was certified platinum shortly after its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://musiccorner.gr/extras/singers/garbi/index.html|title=el:\u039a\u0391\u0399\u03a4\u0397 \u0393\u0391\u03a1\u039c\u03a0\u0397 \u0391\u03c6\u03b9\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1...|date=2004-01-01|publisher=Music Corner Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-21}}</ref> The 2x Platinum certification was a first for both Garbi and Phoebus.<ref name=GarbiMikrofono/>\n\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Greece|title=Atofio Hrysafi|artist=Katy Garbi|type=album|number=2|award=Platinum|relyear=1994|certyear=1994}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Katy Garbi}}\n\n[[Category:1994 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Phoebus (songwriter)]]\n[[Category:Katy Garbi albums]]\n[[Category:Greek-language albums]]\n[[Category:Sony Music Greece albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Atofio Hrysafi<br>\u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9\n| type         = [[Album]]\n| artist       = [[Katy Garbi]]\n| cover        = ATOFIOXRUSAFI.jpg\n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = December 20, 1994\n| recorded     = City studio<br>Sierra studio\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop (music)|Pop]], [[La\u00efka|Modern Laika]], [[Dance music|Dance]]\n| length       = 36:39\n| language     = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music Greece]]<br>[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| producer     = Giannis Doulamis\n| prev_title   = [[Os Ton Paradeiso]]\n| prev_year    = 1993\n| next_title   = [[Arhizo Polemo]]\n| next_year    = 1996\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Atofio Hrysafi\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Ksypoliti Horevo]]\n | single1date = 1994\n | single2     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Atofio Hrysafi]]\n | single2date = 1994\n | single3     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Mi Me Sygkrineis]]\n | single3date = 1995\n | single4     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Kolasi]]\n | single4date = 1995\n | single5     = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]]]\n | single5date = 1995\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' (''trans.'' \u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9; Pure Gold) is an album by popular [[Greece|Greek]] artist [[Katy Garbi]].\n\nIt was released on December 20, 1994 by [[Sony Music|Sony Music Greece]] and was certified 2x Platinum, selling over 120,000 units worldwide.<ref name=\"10+1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.getgreekmusic.gr/diskoi-garbi-afieroma/|title=el:10+1 \u03b1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c0\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9 \u03b4\u03af\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae!|date=2015-04-10|publisher=GetGreekMusic|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-02-12}}</ref> The album contains ten songs, five of which were composed by [[Kostas Tournas]] and five of which were composed by [[Phoebus (songwriter)|Phoebus]].<ref name=\"10+1tralala\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tralala.gr/viografia-keti-garmpi/|title=el:\u0392\u03b9\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1 {{!}} \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae|date=2018-06-08|publisher=Tralala Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-08}}</ref>\n\n== Track List ==\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed = \n| headline = \n| title1 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Ksypoliti Horevo]]\n| note1 = \u039e\u03c5\u03c0\u03cc\u03bb\u03c5\u03c4\u03b7 \u03a7\u03bf\u03c1\u03b5\u03cd\u03c9; I Dance Barefoot\n| lyrics1 = [[Kostas Tournas]]\n| music1 = Kostas Tournas\n| length1 = 4:13\n| title2 = I Agapas I Fevgeis\n| note2 = \u0389 \u0391\u03b3\u03b1\u03c0\u03ac\u03c2 \u0389 \u03a6\u03b5\u03cd\u03b3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2; To Love Or To Leave\n| lyrics2 = Kostas Tournas\n| music2 = Kostas Tournas\n| length2 = 3:11\n| title3 = Oti Oneirevomaste Ginetai\n| note3 = \u038c\u03c4\u03b9 \u039f\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5 \u0393\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9; Whatever Our Dreams Become\n| lyrics3 = Kostas Tournas\n| music3 = Kostas Tournas\n| length3 = 3:11\n| title4 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Mi Me Sygkrineis]]\n| note4 = \u039c\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5 \u03a3\u03c5\u03b3\u03ba\u03c1\u03af\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2; Don't Compare Me\n| lyrics4 = Kostas Tournas\n| music4 = Kostas Tournas\n| length4 = 4:03\n| title5 = Otan Se Ksehaso\n| note5 = \u038c\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd \u03a3\u03b5 \u039e\u03b5\u03c7\u03ac\u03c3\u03c9; When I Forget You\n| lyrics5 = Kostas Tournas\n| music5 = Kostas Tournas\n| length5 = 3:42\n| title6 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]]]\n| note6 = \u03a3\u03b5 \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1 [\u03a0\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a0\u03b5\u03c2]; In Siege [Say It, Say It]\n| lyrics6 = [[Phoebus]]\n| music6 = Phoebus\n| length6 = 3:32\n| title7 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Kolasi]]\n| note7 = \u039a\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7; Hell\n| lyrics7 = Phoebus\n| music7 = Phoebus\n| length7 = 3:29\n| title8 = [[Atofio Hrysafi#Singles|Atofio Hrysafi]]\n| note8 = \u0391\u03c4\u03cc\u03c6\u03b9\u03bf \u03a7\u03c1\u03c5\u03c3\u03ac\u03c6\u03b9; Pure Gold\n| lyrics8 = Phoebus\n| music8 = Phoebus\n| length8 = 3:25\n| title9 = O Ilios Pou Egine Vrohi\n| note9 = \u039f \u0389\u03bb\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 \u03a0\u03bf\u03c5 \u0388\u03b3\u03b9\u03bd\u03b5 \u0392\u03c1\u03bf\u03c7\u03ae; The Sun That Became Rain\n| lyrics9 = Phoebus\n| music9 = Phoebus\n| length9 = 3:47\n| title10 = Moiazo\n| note10 = \u039c\u03bf\u03b9\u03ac\u03b6\u03c9; I Resemble\n| lyrics10 = Phoebus\n| music10 = Phoebus\n| length10 = 4:06\n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Singles and Music Videos ==\nThe following singles were officially released to radio stations and made into music videos.\n\n#\"Ksypoliti Horevo\" <small>(I Dance Barefoot)</small>\n#\"Atofio Hrysafi\" <small>(Pure Gold)</small>\n#\"Mi Me Sygkrineis\" <small>(Don't Compare Me)</small>\n#\"Kolasi\" <small>(Hell)</small>\n#\"Se Poliorkia [Pes, Pes]\" <small>(In Siege [Say It, Say It])</small>\n\n== Credits and Personnel ==\n'''Personnel'''\n\n*<small>Arranged By:</small> Charis Andreadis <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</small>\n*<small>Backing Vocals:</small> Charis Chalkitis <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Nikos Logothetis <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Sofia Noiti <small>(tracks: 6, 8),</small> Poimis Petrou <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Sandy Politi <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Dimitris Tsopanellis <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5),</small> Martha Zioga <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 5)</small>\n*<small>Baglama:</small> Giannis Mpithikotsis <small>(tracks: 9)</small>\n*<small>Bass:</small> Giotis Kiourtsoglou <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 4)</small>\n*<small>Bouzouki:</small> Giannis Mpithikotsis <small>(tracks: 9),</small> Thodoris Pasiaras <small>(tracks: 1, 4)</small>\n*<small>C\u00fcmb\u00fc\u015f:</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 10)</small>\n*<small>Guitars:</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1),</small> Akis Tourkogiorgis <small>(tracks: 2, 3, 4)</small>\n*<small>Keyboards, Programmed By:</small> Stavros Lantsias <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5),</small> Orestis Plakidis <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10)</small>\n*<small>Percussion:</small> Giorgos Notaras <small>(tracks: 1),</small> Giorgos Roilos <small>(tracks: 7, 8)</small>\n*<small>Saxophone:</small> Silvios Siros <small>(tracks: 5)</small>\n*<small>Second Vocal:</small> [[Katy Garbi]] <small>(tracks: 1, 4),</small> Antonis Gounaris <small>(tracks: 7, 9)</small>\n\n\n'''Production'''\n\n*<small>Artwork:</small> Giannis Doxas\n*<small>Executive Producer:</small> Giannis Doulamis\n*<small>Hair Styling:</small> Giannis Michailidis\n*<small>Make Up:</small> Achilleas Charitos\n*<small>Mastering:</small> Giannis Ioannidis [D.P.H.]\n*<small>Photographer:</small> Ntinos Diamantopoulos\n*<small>Recorded By, Mixed By:</small> Dimitris Malegkas [City studio] <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5),</small> Panagiotis Petronikolos [Sierra studio] <small>(tracks: 6, 7, 8, 9, 10),</small> Giannis Tountas [City studio] <small>(tracks: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</small>\n\n== Accolades ==\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' was awarded \"Album of the Year\" at the [[Pop Corn Music Awards of 1995]].<ref name=\"GarbiMikrofono\">{{cite web|url=https://mikrofwno.gr/2019/06/kaiti-garmpi-i-foni-tis-kardias-mas/|title=el:\u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae: \u0397 \u03c6\u03c9\u03bd\u03ae \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b9\u03ac\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2|date=2019-06-01|publisher=Mikrofono Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-08}}</ref> An other award was received for \"Best Folk Dance Track\" (Ksypoliti Horevo) the same year.\n\n==Certifications==\n'''Atofio Hrysafi''' was certified platinum shortly after its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://musiccorner.gr/extras/singers/garbi/index.html|title=el:\u039a\u0391\u0399\u03a4\u0397 \u0393\u0391\u03a1\u039c\u03a0\u0397 \u0391\u03c6\u03b9\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1...|date=2004-01-01|publisher=Music Corner Gr|language=Greek |accessdate=2019-11-21}}</ref> The 2x Platinum certification was a first for both Garbi and Phoebus.<ref name=GarbiMikrofono/>\n\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Greece|title=Atofio Hrysafi|artist=Katy Garbi|type=album|number=2|award=Platinum|relyear=1994|certyear=1994}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Katy Garbi}}\n\n[[Category:1994 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Phoebus (songwriter)]]\n[[Category:Katy Garbi albums]]\n[[Category:Greek-language albums]]\n[[Category:Sony Music Greece albums]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAccolades:Typo fixing, replaced: An other  \u2192 Another", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atofio_Hrysafi"}
{"title_page": "Detroit News Orchestra", "text_new": "[[File:Detroit News Orchestra broadcasting over WWJ - 1922.jpg|thumb|upright 1.2|alt==The Detroit News Orchestra playing in a WWJ radio station studio | Detroit News Orchestra in WWJ radio studio]]\n[[File:Otto E Kruger , c. 1923.jpg|thumb|upright 0.8|Otto Krueger playing a flute |Otto E. Krueger, conductor]]\n\nThe '''Detroit News Orchestra''' was the world's first [[radio orchestra]], first broadcasting in 1922. It was composed of already-distinguished members of the [[Detroit Symphony Orchestra]], broadcasting from [[radio station]] [[WWJ (AM)|WWJ]] in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]]<ref name=\"WWJ\">{{cite web |url=https://detroit.cbslocal.com/2010/06/24/wwj-firsts-timeline/ |title=\"WWJ Firsts\" Timeline |date=June 24, 2010 |publisher=[[WWJ-TV|WWJ - Channel CBS Detroit]] |accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>{{sfn|Kiska|2009|pages=2, 4, 105}}  The orchestra's broadcasts could be received across most of North America and even as far away as Hawaii.{{sfn|Kiska|2009|pages=2, 4, 105}}<ref name=OrchestraHeardHawaii/>\n\n== Background ==\nThe 16 members of the Detroit News Orchestra were drawn from the city's Detroit Symphony Orchestra, having previously achieved distinction as accomplished soloists. The orchestra broadcast on radio station [[WWJ (AM)|WWJ]], first debuting on May&nbsp;28, 1922.<ref name=\"WWJ\"/>{{sfn|Gavrilovich|McGraw|2006|page=62}} The broadcasts were sponsored by [[Detroit Bank & Trust Company|The Detroit Bank]] and could be received across half of North America.{{sfn|Detroit News|1922|page=12}} The Detroit News Orchestra was the first symphonic ensemble in the world organized specifically to play on radio.<ref name=\"WWJ\"/>{{sfn|Sies|2008|page=785}}{{sfn|Kane|Anzovin|Podell|1997|page=30}}\n\nThe Orchestra, sometimes referred to as the \"little symphony,\"<ref name=\"Radio\">{{cite web |url= https://www.americanradiohistory.com/hd2/IDX-Business/Stations/IDX/Station-Books-IDX/WWJ-The-Detroit-News-1922-OCR-Page-0023.pdf |title=The Detroit News Orchestra - American Radio History |page=22 |format=PDF |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref> played at the WWJ Detroit News radio studio from Monday through Friday at 7:00&nbsp;P.M., as well as at 2:00&nbsp;P.M. on Sundays.<ref name=BroadcastDays>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title= First Radio Orchestra |url= https://www.newspapers.com/clip/46691861/ |newspaper=[[Wisconsin State Journal]] |page= 9  |location=Madison, Wisconsin|date= 23 July 1922|via=[[Newspapers.com]] {{open access}} }}</ref> On occasion they also performed recitals for churches, schools, and other non-profit organization as a public relations outreach to their listeners.{{sfn|Fourth Estate|1922|page=26}} WWJ claims to be America's first [[commercial radio station]]{{sfn|Godfrey|Leigh|1998|page=426}} and was also the first radio station to broadcast regular [[radio news]].<ref name=\"WWJ\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailydetroit.com/2016/09/28/10-impressive-detroit-firsts/ |date=September 28, 2016\n|first1=Ardelia |last1=Lee |title=10 Impressive Detroit Firsts |publisher=[[Daily Detroit]] |accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Listeners in Hawaii ==\nOn November&nbsp;23, 1922, at thirty minutes past midnight, the Detroit News Orchestra played the waltz [[Three O'Clock in the Morning|\"Three O'Clock in the Morning]]\" in studio in the [[The Detroit News|Detroit News]] building. The transmission was received clearly at 6:30&nbsp;P.M. local time in the [[Hawaiian Islands]] by A. F. Costa, the postmaster at [[Wailuku, Hawaii]]. Several people listened to the program in its entirety at the Wailuku post office, over 4,400 miles (7,100&nbsp;km) from Detroit. The notes of the music transmitted from the Detroit News radio station in Michigan took about one fiftieth of a second to arrive in Hawaii.<ref name=OrchestraHeardHawaii>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title= Distance Records Broken When Hawaii Picks Up Detroit News |url= https://www.newspapers.com/clip/46742850/  |newspaper= [[The Paducah Sun-Democrat]] |page= 5  |location=Paducah, Kentucky|date= 25 January 1923 |via=[[Newspapers.com]] {{open access}} }}</ref>\n\n== Ensemble ==\n{{multiple image\n | align = right\n | total_width = 700\n | image1 = Detroit News symphonic ensembel 1922.jpg\n | alt1 = Detroit News Orchestra\n | caption1 = <center>Detroit News Orchestra players\n | image2 = WWJ range.jpg\n | alt2 = Map of station WWJ broadcast range\n | caption2 = <center>WWJ broadcast range\n\n | footer = \n}}\n{{clear}}\nList of personnel of the [[musical ensemble]].{{sfn|Detroit News|1922|page=21}}  \n* [[Otto E Krueger]] \u2013 [[conductor]]{{efn-ua|He was a well known member of the Detroit Symphony Orchestra, and also was conductor of the [[Federal Music Project|Works Projects Administration Orchestra]].{{sfn|Detroit News|1922|page=21}} {{sfn|Clemens|2008|page=67}}}}\n* [[Maurice Warner]] \u2013 [[violinist]] and [[Concertmeister]]{{efn-ua|\"Concertmeister; member of [[New York Symphony Orchestra]] on European tour, and soloist throughout United States and Canada; first violin,\nDetroit Symphony Orchestra\"<ref name=\"Radio\"/>}}\n* [[Herman Goldstein (violinist)|Herman Goldstein]] \u2013 violinist  \n* [[LeRoy Hancock]] \u2013 violinist \n* [[Armand Hebert]] \u2013 violinist \n* [[Valbert P. Coffey]] \u2013  [[pianist]] \n* [[Frederick Broeder]] \u2013 [[cellist]] \n* [[Eugene W Braunsdorf]] \u2013 [[Bass violin|bass]] soloist  \n* [[Thomas J Byrne]] \u2013 [[oboe]] soloist  \n* [[R. M. Arey]] \u2013 [[clarinet]]ist   \n* [[Vincenzo Pezzi]] \u2013 [[bassoon]]ist \n* [[Albert Stagliamo]] \u2013 [[horn]] player  \n* [[Edward Clarke (trumpeter)|Edward Clarke]] \u2013 [[trumpeter]]\n* [[Floyd O Hara]] \u2013 trumpeter \n* [[Max Smith (trombonist )|Max Smith]] \u2013 [[trombonist]]\n* [[Arthur Cooper (percussionist)|Arthur Cooper]] \u2013 [[xylophone]] player{{sfn|Fuller|1997|page=422}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[1922 in radio]]\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist|group=upper-alpha}}\n\n===Citations===\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{Commons category|Detroit News Orchestra}} \n* {{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TwQ8sfBoDOwC&pg=PA67 |title=The Works Progress Administration in Detroit |first1=Elizabeth |last1=Clemens |location=Charleston, South Carolina|isbn=9780738551814 |type=Paperback |publisher=[[Arcadia Publishing]] |date=March 31, 2008 |series=Images of America |page=67 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Detroit News|first= |title= WWJ\u2014The Detroit News, The History of Radiophone Broadcasting  | url= https://www.google.com/books/edition/WWJ_The_Detroit_News/h3xIAAAAMAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22Detroit+News+Orchestra%22&printsec=frontcover |date=1922|location=Detroit, Michigan|publisher=[[The Evening News Association]] |newspaper=[[Detroit News]] |quote=}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last= Fourth Estate |first=  |title=Fourth Estate  | url= |date=1922|publisher=[[HarperCollins|Fourth Estate Publishing Company]] |quote=  }}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last= Fuller |first=George Newman |title=[[Michigan History]] |volume=44  | url= |date=1997|publisher= Michigan History Division of the [[Michigan Secretary of State|Department of State]] |quote=  }}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last= Gavrilovich|first=Peter, Editor |first2=Bill, Editor |last2=McGraw|title= The Detroit Almanac: 300 Years of Life in the Motor City  | url= https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=rBoOAQAAMAAJ&dq=Gavrilovich%2C+Peter+%282006%29.+The+Detroit+Almanac.+Detroit+Free+Press.+%22Detroit+News+Orchestra%22&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22Detroit+News+Orchestra%22 |date=2006|location=Detroit, Michigan|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]] \n|edition=2, reprint |isbn=0937247480 |id=ISBN 9780937247488}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last2= Anzovin |first2= Steven |first1=Joseph Nathan |last1=Kane |first3=Janet |last3=Podell  |edition=5th, revised |title=Famous First Facts: A Record of Firs