nres. An interview with Martinez in 2016 saying she thinks the album will be \"more hip hop\" does not suffice. All sourced in the \"Music\" section. -->\n* [[Electropop]]\n* [[Alternative rock|alternative pop]]\n| length       = 46:27\n| label        = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| producer     = * Melanie Martinez <small>([[Executive producer#Music|exec.]])</small>\n* Michael Keenan <small>(also exec.)</small>\n* [[Kinetics & One Love|One Love]]\n| prev_title   = [[Cry Baby (Melanie Martinez album)#Cry Baby's Extra Clutter EP|Cry Baby's Extra Clutter EP]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| next_title   = After School\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc = {{Singles\n|single1=Lunchbox Friends\n|single1date=TBA<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/melanie-martinez/images/5/53/LBF.png/revision/latest?cb=20200108105548|title=Are you pushing any singles from K-12??|website=Vignette Wikia}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''K-12''''' (pronounced \"K through twelve\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation|title=Melanie Martinez - K-12 (Official Trailer)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xMJNm24n4Ok|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref><ref name=\"Idolator\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7870647/film-review-melanie-martinez-k-12|title=Film Review: Melanie Martinez's 'K-12' Is A Twisted Pop Musical|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=2019-09-04|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref>) is the second studio album by American singer [[Melanie Martinez]]. It is her first studio album in four years and was released with an accompanying film of the same name on September 6, 2019,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MelanieLBBH/status/1133765575048617984|title=K-12 \ud83d\udc97 SEPT 6|via=[[Twitter]]|date=May 29, 2019|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref> through [[Atlantic Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsday.com/entertainment/columnists/glenn-gamboa/melanie-martinez-new-album-1.31423989|title=LI Sound: Melanie Martinez readying new album, movie|website=[[Newsday]]|last=Gamboa|first=Glenn|date=May 23, 2019|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nMartinez began writing the album in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://isdb.pw/littlebodybigheart/1828647066697942262|title=littlebodybigheart Instagram Stories|website=ISDB PW|date= July 22, 2018|accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.idolator.com/7872524/melanie-martinez-interview-k-12?andro=1&ios=1&safari=1|title= Interview: Melanie Martinez On \u2018K-12\u2019 & Stepping Into Her Power|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=September 6, 2019|accessdate=October 8, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"V Magazine\">{{cite web|url= https://vmagazine.com/article/the-second-coming-of-melanie-martinez/|title= The Second Coming Of Melanie Martinez|last= Rosenzweig|first=Mathias|date=September 14, 2019|work=[[V (American magazine)|V Magazine]]|accessdate=October 14, 2019}}</ref> In a 2017 interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', Martinez said that her then-untitled second album was finished and would be accompanied by a film that she was writing and directing.<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7904990/melanie-martinez-interview-cry-baby-second-album|title=Melanie Martinez Celebrates 'Cry Baby' Chart Success, Looks Ahead To Elaborate Album/Film Project|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|date=August 15, 2017|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref> In a February 2019 [[Instagram]] post, she wrote that the album \"had been done for like two and a half years now\", that it would likely be released at the end of summer and that no singles would be commercially released from it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bt8EddMgG-B/|title=Been dying to give you all an Album/Movie update...|via=[[Instagram]]|date=February 16, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 7, 2020, Martinez announced through her Instagram stories that she will be releasing an EP titled ''After School'' that is attached to the ''K-12'' era. It is set to be released sometime in the spring of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7905236/melanie-martinez-teases-new-ep-which-is-probably-called-after-school?chrome=1|title=Melanie Martinez Teases New EP, Which Is Probably Called \u2018After School\u2019|website=Idolator|last=Wass|first=Mike|language=en|date=2020-01-08|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thetartan.org/2020/2/17/pillbox/martinez|title=Melanie Martinez - After School|website=The Tartan|last=Kim|first=Madeline|language=en|date=2020-02-16|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Martinez also previously revealed that she has planned two more films, both of which will be accompanied by albums.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/melanie-martinez/news/k-12-movie-sequel/|title=Melanie Martinez reveals plans for two more movies after K-12|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=2019-09-21}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nA teaser video of Martinez in a [[Pastel (color)|pastel]] classroom was released on May 15, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/melanie-martinez-k12-teaser/|title=Melanie Martinez teases 'K-12' era with eerie video, album art|work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref> On May 16, she unveiled the album cover through her social media accounts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7775880/melanie-martinez-teases-sophomore-album-k-12|title=She's Back! Melanie Martinez Teases Sophomore LP, 'K-12'|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=May 15, 2019|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref> Martinez revealed the release date through Instagram on May 29.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/stories/littlebodybigheart/|title=Stories \u2022 littlebodybigheart|via=[[Instagram]]|date=May 29, 2019|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn June 18, a TV spot was released, which included a snippet of \"Nurse's Office\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rrPcbXr9h0c|title=Melanie Martinez - K-12 (TV Spot)|via=[[YouTube]]|date=June 17, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref> This was followed by weekly promotions, or \"assignments\", beginning in late June 2019, followed by snippets usually a few hours or a day later. Despite no singles being released from the album, Martinez released snippets along with respective animated videos for every song from the album to different location hotspots called \"assignments,\" later uploading them to her social media and YouTube accounts.<ref name=\"lbf tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1143181452823224323|title=Snippet of Lunchbox Friends, from my album K-12 coming sept 6 \u2728 \ud83d\udc98Artwork: @pastelae|date=June 24, 2019|accessdate=June 25, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"principal tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1146056375983910912|title=Snippet of 'The Principal' off my album K-12! Coming sept 6Artwork: @pastelae 'You don't know the pain that you are causing, yeah your actions hurt so do your words.The more you try to fuck us over we will be there yelling at your front door.|date=July 2, 2019|accessdate=July 3, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"detention tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1148638113918574593|title=\u2728Snippet of \"Detention\" off of my album K-12! \u2728\"Baby can you meet me tonight in detention? I can feel your blood pressure rise, fuck this tension. Let me crawl up into your mind, did I mention? Pretending everything's alright is detention.\"|date=July 9, 2019|accessdate=July 9, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"recess tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1151220112289980419|title=\ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffcSnippet of \"Recess\" off my album K-12! \ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffc Artwork: @pastelae \ud83d\udc97|date=July 16, 2019|accessdate=July 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1153334116408016899|title=Snippet of \"High School Sweethearts\" off my album K-12! \ud83c\udf6b\ud83c\udf39|date=July 22, 2019|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1156974381173751809|title=\u2728Snippet of \u201cWheels On The Bus\u201d from K-12\u2728  \"I'm saying nothing, No one's watching us don't give a fuck wheels on the bus.  I'm holding it down up in the front, wheels on the bus. Ooh.\"|date=August 1, 2019|accessdate=August 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|title=\ud83d\udc97Snippet of \u201cClass Fight\u201d off my album K-12!\ud83d\udc97 Artwork: @pastelae \ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffc Pre-order K-12: melanie.lnk.to/K-12TA|number=1159434460116529154|date=August 8, 2019|accessdate=August 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1162107901764349952|title=Snippet of \"Teacher's Pet\" off my album K-12 coming out in 22 days!\ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffc\ud83d\udc97|date=August 15, 2019|accessdate=August 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1163563983389024258|title=\ud83d\udc95Snippet of \u201cShow & Tell\u201d off K-12! \ud83d\udc95 \u201cWhy is it so hard to see? If I cut myself I would bleed. I\u2019m just like you, you\u2019re like me. Imperfect and human are we.\u201d Artwork: @pastelae \u2728\ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffc Pre-order K-12: melanie.lnk.to/K-12TA|date=August 19, 2019|accessdate=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1165225196984385536|title=\ud83d\udc97Snippet of \u201cDrama Club\u201d off K-12!\ud83d\udc97Artwork: Pastelae Pre-order K-12 out September 6: https://melanie.lnk.to/K-12TW|date=August 24, 2019|accessdate=August 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1166729187006267398|title=Snippet of my personal favorite, \"Nurse's Office\" off my album K-12! Coming out in 9 fucking days!\ud83d\udc97\ud83d\udc7c\ud83c\udffc Pre-order: https://melanie.lnk.to/K-12TA Artwork: Pastelae|date=August 28, 2019|accessdate=August 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=MelanieLBBH|number=1168523978849341440|title=\ud83d\udc95 Snippet of \"Orange Juice\" off my album K-12 \ud83d\udc95 Coming out in 4 days!!!! Pre-order: https://melanie.lnk.to/K-12TA  Artwork: @Pastelae\ud83d\udc7c|date=September 1, 2019|accessdate=September 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Martinez |first1=Melanie |title=\ud83d\udc97 Snippet of \"Strawberry Shortcake\" off my album K-12 \ud83d\udc97 Coming out in 2 fucking days!!!! |url=https://twitter.com/MelanieLBBH/status/1169265535437197318 |website=Twitter |accessdate=4 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn July 23, the official trailer for the ''K-12'' film was released alongside the album tracklist and pre-order. It reveals some of the plot, while a snippet of \"Show & Tell\" plays at the end of the trailer. It also reveals that the film would be [[limited release|released in select theatres for one day only]] on September 5, 2019.<ref name=\":0\" /> Martinez will embark on the [[K-12 Tour]] in support of the album from October to December 2019, starting in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=\"LNE\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livenationentertainment.com/2019/07/melanie-martinez-announces-the-k-12-tour/|title=Melanie Martinez Announces 'The K-12 Tour'|website=Live Nation Entertainment|date=July 29, 2019|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = K-12\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| director       = Melanie Martinez<br />Alissa Torvinen {{small|(co-director)}}\n| producer       = Julie Greenwald<br />Craig Kallman<br />Phil Botti<br />Ron Shapiro<br />Wes Teshome<br />Kim Stuckwisch<br />Gergely Varga<br />Tyler Zelinsky\n| writer         = Melanie Martinez\n| starring       = Melanie Martinez<br />Emma Harvey\n| music          = Melanie Martinez<br />Michael Keenan\n| cinematography = Josh McKie\n| editing        = Emilie Aubrey<br />Niles Howard\n| distributor    = [[Karol Martesko-Fenster|Abramorama]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|9|5}}\n| runtime        = 95 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/k-12-film|title=K-12|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|access-date=September 10, 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $5-6 million<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bell |first1=BreAnna |title=How Atlantic Records Helped Bring Melanie Martinez\u2019s Film Fantasy to Life |url=http://variety.com/2019/film/news/melanie-martinez-movie-k-12-budget-atlantic-records-1203323613/amp/ |website=Variety |accessdate=11 September 2019}}</ref>\n| gross          = $360,000{{small|(reflects selected countries only)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=k12.htm|title=K-12 (2019)|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|access-date=September 10, 2019}}</ref> \n}}\n===Singles===\nMartinez announced in January 2020, months after the album's release, that \"Lunchbox Friends\" would be pushed as the first single off of the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/melanie-martinez/images/5/53/LBF.png/revision/latest?cb=20200108105548|title=Are you pushing any singles from K-12??|website=Vignette Wikia}}</ref>\n\n====Promotional singles====\nPrior to the announcement that \"Lunchbox Friends\" would be the first official single, Martinez pushed both \"High School Sweethearts\" and \"Strawberry Shortcake\" as promotional singles in July 2019 via vinyl release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://store.melaniemartinezmusic.com/k-12/k-12-exclusive-mint-colored-vinyl-1.html|title=K-12 (Exclusive Mint Colored Vinyl)|website=Melaniemartinez.com|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n''K-12'' was mostly produced by Michael Keenan, who had previously collaborated with Martinez on a few tracks on her previous album, ''Cry Baby''. One track, \"Drama Club\", was co-written and produced by Martinez's frequent collaborators, [[Kinetics & One Love]]. ''K-12'' is primarily an [[electropop]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wilbur |first1=Macy |title=Review: Melanie Martinez unveils the darker side of school in\u201cK-12\u201d |url=https://dailyfreepress.com/blog/2019/09/08/review-melanie-martinez-unveils-the-darker-side-of-school-ink-12/ |website=The Daily Free Press |accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref> and [[Alternative rock|alternative pop]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Barzola |first1=Brandon |title=Melanie Martinez returns with new music and movie, 'K-12' |url=https://dailycampus.com/stories/2019/9/10/melanie-martinez-returns-with-new-music-and-movie-k-12nbsp |website=The Daily Campus |accessdate=24 December 2019}}</ref> record. Martinez's official website describes the album's sound as \"a vibrant and singular melting pot of low-key [[Hip hop music|hip-hop]], soulful [[Pop music|pop]] and indie-leaning [[Electro (music)|electro]]\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Melanie Martinez - K-12 - About |url=https://www.melaniemartinezmusic.com/ |website=Melanie Martinez Music |accessdate=9 September 2019}}</ref> [[AllMusic]] also notes influences of hip hop and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]].<ref name=\"AllMusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/k-12-mw0003303358|title=K-12 \u2013 Melanie Martinez|publisher=AllMusic|last=Collar|first=Matt|accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AllMusic\"/>\n}}\n\nIn a positive review, Mike Wass from [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] described the film as a \"twisted pop musical\". He praised the \"seamless\" integration of the album's music into the film's plot and compared the visuals to those found in [[Tim Burton]] and [[Wes Anderson]]'s films, but described the content as \"multi-layered, gritty and distinctly Melanie\". He stated, \"Melanie has created a cohesive, funny, empowering film from scratch \u2014 and also delivered 13 bops.\" and found \"Wheels on the Bus\" (which he described as an \"earworm\"), \"High School Sweethearts\" and \"Lunchbox Friends\" to be standout album tracks. He ended the review by advising the reader to \"[watch] the film before listening to the album to get the full experience. After all, that's the way Melanie intended this era to be consumed.\"<ref name=\"Idolator\" />\n\n==Commercial performance==\nDespite no singles being released prior to the album, ''K-12'' debuted at number three on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 57,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, of which 30,000 were pure album sales. It is Martinez's second US top-10 album.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8530004/post-malone-hollywoods-bleeding-No1-debut-billboard-200-chart|title=Post Malone Scores Second No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 With 'Hollywood's Bleeding'|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=September 15, 2019|accessdate=September 16, 2019}}</ref> and her highest charting album on the chart to date. Additionally it topped the alternative album chart becoming her second consecutive top charter. Elsewhere the album reached the top 10 of eight different countries including the UK, Australia and Canada. The album has sold 264,900 units in the US, including 56,421 pure sales.<!-- Please do not change until Rolling Stone 200 is finalised --><ref>Combined [[album-equivalent unit]]s from the {{citeweb|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/albums/2019-09-06/|publisher=[[Rolling Stone]]|title=Rolling Stone Top 200|date= January 11, 2020|accessdate= January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAdapted from [[Apple Music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/k-12/1473836491|title=K-12 by Melanie Martinez|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title1 = Wheels on the Bus\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Melanie Martinez]]|Michael Keenan|[[Emily Warren]]}}\n| extra1 = \n| length1 = 3:40\n| title2 = Class Fight\n| writer2 = \n| extra2 = \n| length2 = 2:41\n| tit