emartinezmusic.com/k-12.html|title=K-12|website=melaniemartinezmusic.com|accessdate=September 11, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Melanie Martinez}}\n\n[[Category:2019 albums]]\n[[Category:Melanie Martinez (singer) albums]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records albums]]\n[[Category:Electropop albums]]\n", "name_user": "212.224.227.102", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K-12_(album)"}
{"title_page": "Australian Council of Social Service", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Australian Council of Social Service\n| logo = Australian_Council_of_Social_Service_Logo.png\n| type = Non-profit\n| industry = \n| fate = \n| founded = {{Start date and age|1956}}\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Strawberry Hills, New South Wales]]\n| hq_location_country = Australia\n| area_served = Australia\n| key_people = {{Unbulleted list|\nTony Reidy (President)|\nHang Vo (Vice President)}}\n| website = {{URL|acoss.org.au}}\n}}\nThe '''Australian Council of Social Service''' ('''ACOSS''') is an Australian organisation that advocates for action to reduce [[poverty in Australia|poverty]] and [[Social inequality|inequality]], and is the peak body for the community services sector in Australia. It was formed in 1956.<ref>Philip Mendes ''Inside the Welfare Lobby: A History of the Australian Council of Social Service''</ref>\n\nACOSS is active in areas of [[social policy]], including [[community sector]] policy, [[climate and energy]], [[economics]] and [[taxation in Australia|tax]], income support and [[employment]], [[health in Australia|health]], [[housing]] and [[homelessness in Australia|homelessness]], and [[poverty in Australia|poverty]] and [[economic inequality|inequality]].  \n\nThe current ACOSS CEO is Dr Cassandra Goldie who was previously the Director of the Sex Discrimination Unit at the [[HREOC|Australian Human Rights Commission (HREOC)]].\n\nThe ACOSS CEO is often interviewed by [[Media of Australia|Australian media]] for comment and analysis on social matters and policies of the [[Government of Australia]].\n\n==Governance==\nACOSS has a 9-person volunteer Board of Governors, elected according to the [http://www.acoss.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ACOSS-Rules-of-Association-Adopted-9-August-2017.pdf Rules of Association] adopted in August 2017.\n\n==Presidents==\n* January 2016 - current: Tony Reidy\n* January 2015 - December 2016: Micaela Cronin\n* December 2013 - January 2015: Francis Lynch\n* November 2009 \u2013 November 2013: Simon Schrapel\n* May\u2013November 2009: David Thompson (interim)\n* 2005-May 2009: [[Lin Hatfield Dodds]]\n* 2001-2005: [[Andrew McCallum]]\n* 1997-2000: [[Michael Raper]]\n* 1993-1997: Robert Fitzgerald \n* 1989-1993: Merle Mitchell\n* 1985-1989: Julian Disney\n\n==Members==\n\n===State and Territory Councils of Social Service===\n* ACT Council of Social Service (ACTCOSS)\n* NSW Council of Social Service (NCOSS)\n* South Australian Council of Social Service (SACOSS)\n* Northern Territory Council of Social Service (NTCOSS)\n* Queensland Council of Social Service (QCOSS)\n* Tasmanian Council of Social Service (TasCOSS)\n* Victorian Council of Social Service (VCOSS)\n* Western Australia Council of Social Service (WACOSS)\n\n===National organisation members===\n* Adult Learning Australia\n* AIDS Trust of Australia\n* [[Anglicare|Anglicare Australia]]\n* [[Australian Association of Social Workers]]\n* Australian Baha\u2019i Community\n* Australian Catholic Social Justice Council\n* Australian Council of State School Organisations\n* [[Australian Federation of AIDS Organisations]]\n* Australian Federation of Disability Organisations\n* Australian Men\u2019s Health Forum\n* Australian Neighbourhood Houses & Centres Association\n* [[Australian Psychological Society]]\n* [[Australian Red Cross]]\n* [[Australian Unemployed Workers' Union]]\n* [[Australian Youth Affairs Coalition]]\n* Baptist Care Australia\n* [[Brotherhood of St Laurence]]\n* Carers Australia\n* [[Catholic Social Services Australia]]\n* Children and Young People with Disability Australia\n* Community Colleges Australia\n* Community Housing Industry Association\n* Community Mental Health Australia\n* Consumers Health Forum of Australia\n* COTA Australia\n* Disability Advocacy Network Australia\n* Down Syndrome Australia \n* Family Relationship Services Australia\n* Federation of Ethic Communities\