\n| hq_location_city = [[Strawberry Hills, New South Wales]]\n| hq_location_country = Australia\n| area_served = Australia\n| key_people = {{Unbulleted list|\nTony Reidy (President)|\nHang Vo (Vice President)}}\n| website = {{URL|acoss.org.au}}\n}}\nThe '''Australian Council of Social Service''' ('''ACOSS''') is an Australian organisation that advocates for action to reduce [[poverty in Australia|poverty]] and [[inequality]], and is the peak body for the community services sector in Australia. It was formed in 1956.<ref>Philip Mendes ''Inside the Welfare Lobby: A History of the Australian Council of Social Service''</ref>\n\nACOSS is active in areas of [[social policy]], including [[community sector]] policy, [[climate and energy]], [[economics]] and [[taxation in Australia|tax]], income support and [[employment]], [[health in Australia|health]], [[housing]] and [[homelessness in Australia|homelessness]], and [[poverty in Australia|poverty]] and [[economic inequality|inequality]].  \n\nThe current ACOSS CEO is Dr Cassandra Goldie who was previously the Director of the Sex Discrimination Unit at the [[HREOC|Australian Human Rights Commission (HREOC)]].\n\nThe ACOSS CEO is often interviewed by [[Media of Australia|Australian media]] for comment and analysis on social matters and policies of the [[Government of Australia]].\n\n==Governance==\nACOSS has a 9-person volunteer Board of Governors, elected according to the [http://www.acoss.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ACOSS-Rules-of-Association-Adopted-9-August-2017.pdf Rules of Association] adopted in August 2017.\n\n==Presidents==\n* January 2016 - current: Tony Reidy\n* January 2015 - December 2016: Micaela Cronin\n* December 2013 - January 2015: Francis Lynch\n* November 2009 \u2013 November 2013: Simon Schrapel\n* May\u2013November 2009: David Thompson (interim)\n* 2005-May 2009: [[Lin Hatfield Dodds]]\n* 2001-2005: [[Andrew McCallum]]\n* 1997-2000: [[Michael Raper]]\n* 1993-1997: Robert Fitzgerald \n* 1989-1993: 